com.mokiat.data.front.common

Class OBJLimits

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mokiat.data.front.common.OBJLimits

  • public class OBJLimits
extends Object
    The OBJLimits class can be used to specify parsing limits for OBJ resources.

    Properly configuring an instance of this class and passing it to parsers allows one to prevent OutOfMemoryError errors.

    Author:
    Momchil Atanasov
